# Two-way email initiative context

When the user is editing files under **`docs/initiatives/two-way-email/`** or the canonical PRD **`docs/prds/india-candidate-profile-email-conversation-prd.md`**:

1. **Read first:** [`docs/initiatives/two-way-email/CONTEXT.md`](docs/initiatives/two-way-email/CONTEXT.md) — manifest of PRD, transcripts (under `transcripts/`), [decisions.md](docs/initiatives/two-way-email/decisions.md), research, design, and backlog pointers.
2. **Source of truth:** Requirements live in the PRD linked from that manifest; do not contradict it without an explicit PM request to revise the PRD.
3. **Functional grounding:** Use **050** (`050-functional-knowledge.mdc`) and `functional-knowledge/`; use MCPs as documented in **000** (`000-master-orchestrator.mdc`).
4. **Backlog / stories:** Use **400**, **420**, **430** with the PRD as input; mission handoff row **INDIA-E2E-006** in `MISSION_LOG.md` lists related artefacts.
5. **Jira story drafting (430 hand-in-hand):** When creating or rewriting **Jira** stories for this initiative, read [`docs/initiatives/two-way-email/STORY_WRITING_SUPPLEMENT.md`](docs/initiatives/two-way-email/STORY_WRITING_SUPPLEMENT.md) **in addition to** **430** — it holds HRREC-82977-specific summaries, default **Notes** (Figma + PRD), Message Builder vs Recruiting chrome vocabulary, and wiki examples. **430** stays the universal workflow (wiki, DoR, Step 1c, **319**).
6. **Net-new gap review (`/user-story-gap-review`):** When the scope is **HRREC-82977** / two-way email, read [`docs/initiatives/two-way-email/COMPANION_WHATSAPP_EPICS.md`](docs/initiatives/two-way-email/COMPANION_WHATSAPP_EPICS.md) and run the **Companion channel cross-scan** on **every** such gap-review run (**mandatory**): canonical WhatsApp epic keys, URLs, disclaimers, and **manifest-only** reading of [`docs/initiatives/two-way-email/reference/WHATSAPP_COMPANION_CORPUS_SNAPSHOT.md`](docs/initiatives/two-way-email/reference/WHATSAPP_COMPANION_CORPUS_SNAPSHOT.md) when eligible (`manifest_complete: true`); opt-in **`WhatsApp live delta`** / **`WhatsApp refresh corpus`** for live Jira delta with snapshot; otherwise **full Story+Bug + `getTicketDetails` per key** if the user says **`WhatsApp live-only`** / **`ignore WhatsApp snapshot`** or the snapshot is ineligible (unless the user narrows scope)—pattern hints only, not requirements for email. **Explicit opt-out** if the user truly wants email-only analysis: **`no WhatsApp companion`**, **`skip companion cross-scan`**, **`omit WhatsApp companion`**, or **`2WE email only`** (see [`.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference-companion-whatsapp.md`](.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference-companion-whatsapp.md) **When to run**). For **subset / smoke** HRREC-82977 runs (first N keys, local HTML, or “do not overwrite rolling Confluence”), follow [`.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference.md`](.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference.md) **Subset / smoke / local-only runs** so publish target and Tier A per-row evidence stay explicit; **companion step 2b still runs** unless the user opted out above. **Optional Companion Peanut anchor pass** (git-level evidence on **3–8** named WhatsApp keys only, megaleo repos with **full history**, `JIRA_TOKEN` for Peanut MCP): see [`.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference-companion-whatsapp.md`](.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference-companion-whatsapp.md) (**Optional Peanut** + operator preflight)—default companion work stays Jira/snapshot grounded without Peanut on the whole manifest. The Confluence page’s holistic **Possible missing stories** (three-column suggestions) table is specified in [`.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference.md`](.cursor/skills/user-story-gap-review/reference.md) **Possible missing stories (holistic suggestions)**.
7. **Design / compose prototype:** When working under `design/**/*` on the profile email compose path, **012** (`012-conversational-email-compose-mvp.mdc`) defines MVP exclusions (templates, GenAI on compose toolbar, etc.) — do not restore those without explicit PM approval.
